  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol in envoyproxy/envoy is implemented across multiple C++ source files organized in the source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc directory.\n\nCore Components:\n\n1. GrpcSubscriptionImpl Adapter (grpc_subscription_impl.h/.cc): This class adapts typed Subscription interfaces to the untyped GrpcMux interface. It handles per-xDS API stats/logging and acts as a bridge between the subscription API and the multiplexing layer.\n\n2. GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory (grpc_subscription_factory.h/.cc): This factory class implements the selection logic between SotW (State of the World) and Delta xDS modes. It checks the runtime feature flag 'envoy.reloadable_features.unified_mux' to decide which implementation to use. When unified_mux is enabled, it instantiates GrpcMuxSotw or GrpcMuxDelta from the new xds_mux namespace; otherwise, it uses the legacy GrpcMuxImpl or NewGrpcMuxImpl.\n\n3. Unified XdsMux Template (xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc): This is the modern, unified implementation using a template-based architecture. The template class GrpcMuxImpl<S, F, RQ, RS> is parameterized with:\n   - S: SubscriptionState type (SotwSubscriptionState or DeltaSubscriptionState)\n   - F: SubscriptionStateFactory type\n   - RQ: Request message type (DiscoveryRequest or DeltaDiscoveryRequest)\n   - RS: Response message type (DiscoveryResponse or DeltaDiscoveryResponse)\n   \n   Two concrete implementations are provided:\n   - GrpcMuxSotw: For State of the World protocol\n   - GrpcMuxDelta: For Delta xDS protocol\n\n4. Subscription State Implementations (xds_mux/ directory):\n   - subscription_state.h: Contains the BaseSubscriptionState template base class that handles protocol state tracking\n   - sotw_subscription_state.h/.cc: Implements State of the World protocol logic, tracking version_info and nonces\n   - delta_subscription_state.h/.cc: Implements Delta xDS protocol logic, tracking per-resource versions and resource state\n   \n   Both include factory classes (SotwSubscriptionStateFactory and DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory) for creating subscription state instances.\n\n5. Legacy Implementations (for backward compatibility when unified_mux feature is disabled):\n   - grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc: Legacy GrpcMuxImpl for SotW protocol\n   - new_grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc: Legacy NewGrpcMuxImpl for Delta protocol\n\nProtocol Flow: When a subscription is created, GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory creates a GrpcSubscriptionImpl wrapper around a GrpcMux instance. The GrpcMux manages the gRPC stream and multiplexes messages from multiple resource subscriptions. Each subscription type has its own SubscriptionState object that manages the protocol state (SotW or Delta variant). The SubscriptionState objects interact with the GrpcMux through callbacks and request/response handling.\n\nThe unified template design allows both SotW and Delta variants to share common infrastructure (stream management, pausing/resuming, failover handling) while keeping protocol-specific logic isolated in their respective SubscriptionState implementations."
}

